The paper deals with temporal logics for data words, which are a type of formal language. This falls under the scope of formal languages and automata theory, which is typically categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the use of data automata, which is a type of data structure commonly used in computer science, and thus could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of operators for navigation into the future and past, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence and planning, and thus could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of the basic logic with a certain UNTIL-operator, which is a topic in programming languages and formal methods, and thus could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
